cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If honest-scholar supported your research, please disclose your AI use (see
  DISCLOSURE.md) and cite this repository. A citable arXiv report is planned; when
  it exists it will become the preferred citation.
title: honest-scholar
abstract: >-
  A Claude Code plugin for honest, defensible AI-assisted research: the researcher
  makes and signs off every material decision (agency) and must be able to explain
  and defend the work (understanding); the tool keeps the accounts, advises, and
  probes.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Runje
    given-names: Davor
    email: davor.runje@fer.hr
repository-code: "https://github.com/davorrunje/honest-scholar"
url: "https://github.com/davorrunje/honest-scholar"
version: 0.1.0
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - research integrity
  - AI in research
  - reproducibility
  - scientific method
  - honest AI use
